---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Saco Dispensary Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Saco Dispensary Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Understanding the cannabis business regulations in Saco, Maine. Local retail prohibition, manufacturing opportunities, and market analysis."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Saco Cannabis Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating the cannabis industry in Saco, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Regulatory Notice: Retail Prohibition" type="tip">
      As of March 2026, **Saco does not permit adult-use (recreational) retail marijuana stores.** While the city is a hub for other cannabis activities, those looking to open a recreational storefront should consider nearby <a href="/guides/biddeford-dispensary-guide/">Biddeford</a> or <a href="/guides/old-orchard-beach-dispensary-guide/">Old Orchard Beach</a>.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Saco occupies a strategic position in York County, serving as a gateway between Portland and the southern Maine beaches. While the city has opted into specific categories of the cannabis supply chain—most notably manufacturing—it currently maintains a prohibition on recreational retail stores. For entrepreneurs, this makes Saco an ideal location for the "behind-the-scenes" side of the industry rather than customer-facing retail.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Manufacturing Hub" type="passion">
      Saco's industrial zones are becoming a hotspot for cannabis manufacturing. If your passion lies in extraction, edibles, or product development, Saco offers a professional environment with excellent transit access to the rest of the state.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Current Status: What is Allowed?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturing</strong> - Saco allows adult-use manufacturing, particularly when co-located with existing medical facilities.</li>
        <li><strong>Medical Operations</strong> - Saco continues to support the established medical cannabis community.</li>
        <li><strong>Recreational Retail</strong> - ❌ **PROHIBITED.** Retail storefronts for recreational use are not currently permitted.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Saco Market Snapshot</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>19,000+</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Seasonal Traffic</td><td>High (I-95 and Route 1 gateway)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Retail Status</td><td>Prohibited</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Key Strength</td><td>Product Manufacturing & Logistics</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 1</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Strategic Path for Saco</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>**Focus on the Supply Chain:** Target the <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-extraction-licensing/">manufacturing sector</a> where Saco has opted in.</li>
        <li>**Medical Licensing:** Explore medical dispensary paths if you wish to serve the local patient community.</li>
        <li>**Logistics Advantage:** Use Saco's location for efficient distribution to the southern Maine coastal markets.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.sacomaine.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">City of Saco Official Website</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This guide is for informational purposes only. Municipal rules are subject to change. Consult with Saco's Planning Department for current zoning specifics.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
